en: Typical C.C.C barracks and headquarters, 223rd Co. C.C.C., TVA P-10, Powell Station, Tennessee

This photograph provides a view of the facilities of the Civilian Conservation Corps camp of the 223rd Company, TVA P-10, in Powell Station, Tennessee. It includes the typical C.C.C barracks and headquarters. Otto F. Haslbauer donated this photograph, which was printed by Spencer and Wyckoff of Detroit, Michigan.
